# Generated extraction artifacts: large, deterministic, pretty-printed JSON
# data files produced by the state `extract_*.py` adapters (e.g.
# ingestion/states/colorado/extracted/big-game-2026.json is ~104k lines). They
# are committed as durable text-side fixtures (consumed by the loaders and the
# artifact-regression tests), but they are NOT human-reviewed source.
#
# - `-diff`            : treat as binary for diffs, so `git diff` / `--numstat`
#                        report no line-by-line changes. This keeps the change
#                        out of line-count-based review limits (cubic's 50k
#                        changed-line cap) and out of noisy 100k-line diffs.
# - `linguist-generated`: mark as generated so GitHub collapses them in PRs and
#                        excludes them from language statistics.
#
# Regenerate with the relevant `extract_*.py`; never hand-edit. The committed
# content is still version-controlled — only its textual diff is suppressed.
ingestion/states/*/extracted/*.json -diff linguist-generated
